<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1268,1694]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1268,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus box="[412,510,1268,1293]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">holotype</typeStatus>
and female allotype are inaccessible (
<collectionCode box="[960,1019,1268,1292]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/804h-arc5" name="Indian Forest Research Institute" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">IFRI</collectionCode>
). However, Schedl provided a clear description of the species, and in addition, we have examined a drawing of the elytral declivity (
<collectionCode box="[1248,1323,1304,1328]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">NMW</collectionCode>
) made by Schedl from the 
<typeStatus box="[360,462,1340,1365]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">holotype</typeStatus>
. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[739,793,1341,1364]" name="Laos" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[863,963,1340,1365]" name="Thailand" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(see below) agree with both Beeson’s description and the drawing. The species is clearly related to 
<taxonomicName box="[874,1048,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[874,1048,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Platypus lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1307,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Crossotarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psilacanthurus">
<emphasis box="[1110,1307,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">P. psilacanthurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has the characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[301,399,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,399,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Platypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName box="[456,635,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carchesiopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,635,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Carchesiopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is here transferred to 
<emphasis box="[935,1041,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<taxonomicName box="[935,1037,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platypus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
